                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">Copy.</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\"><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>\n            <p>At a meeting of the Congregation Keneseth<lb/> Israel, held <date>April 17<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1854</date>, at the<lb/> Committee rooms, in\n                    <placeName>New Market<lb/> Street, above Noble</placeName>, the following\n                pre-<lb/>amble and resolutions were proposed<lb/> and unanimously adopted:</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Whereas, On the occasion of the<lb/> consecration of our new\n                Synagogue we<lb/> have derived such great benefit from various Gentlemen, on whose\n                kindness<lb/> and assistance we had no other claim<lb/> than that of charity, that\n                we deem it<lb/> expedient and proper to express our<lb/> thanks to them in this\n                manner.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Be it therefore. Resolved. That<lb/> the thanks of the congregation\n                are<lb/> due, to the <persName>Rev. Isaac Leeser</persName>, for<lb/> the excellent\n                sermon which he delivered<lb/> on the occasion, to the <persName>Rev.\n                    Fraenkel</persName>,<lb/>\n                <persName>Rev. S. Morais</persName>, <persName>Rev. Pope</persName> and\n                    <persName>Rev.<lb/> Fassbender</persName> for the services they so</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3m61c94j/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
